#: ../../B/B1FF.rst:9
msgid ""
"The most famous :ref:`pseudo`\\, and the prototypical :ref:`newbie`\\. "
"Articles from B1FF feature all uppercase letters sprinkled liberally with "
"bangs, typos, ‘cute’ misspellings (EVRY BUDY LUVS GOOD OLD BIFF CUZ KØØL "
"DOOD AN HE RITES REEL AWESUM THINGZ IN CAPITULL LETTRS LIKE THIS!!! ), use "
"(and often misuse) of fragments of :ref:`talk-mode` abbreviations, a long "
":ref:`sig-block` (sometimes even a :ref:`doubled-sig`\\), and unbounded "
"naivete. B1FF posts articles using his elder brother's VIC-20. B1FF's "
"location is a mystery, as his articles appear to come from a variety of "
"sites. However, BITNET seems to be the most frequent origin. The theory that"
" B1FF is a denizen of BITNET is supported by B1FF's (unfortunately invalid) "
"electronic mail address: B1FF\\@BIT.NET."
msgstr ""
"最も有名な\\ :ref:`pseudo`\\ であり、\\ :ref:`newbie`\\ "
"の典型。B1FFの記事は、感嘆符をふんだんに散りばめた全部大文字、タイプミス、‘かわいい’綴り間違い(EVRY BUDY LUVS GOOD OLD "
"BIFF CUZ KØØL DOOD AN HE RITES REEL AWESUM THINGZ IN CAPITULL LETTRS LIKE "
"THIS!!! )、\\ :ref:`talk-mode`\\ の略語の断片の使用(しばしば誤用)、長い\\ :ref:`sig-block`\\ "
"(時には\\ :ref:`doubled-sig`\\ "
"まで)、そして果てしない世間知らずぶりを特徴とする。B1FFは兄のVIC-20を使って記事を投稿する。彼の記事はさまざまなサイトから来ているように見えるため、B1FFの所在は謎である。とはいえ、最も多い発信元はBITNETのようだ。B1FFがBITNETの住人だという説は、B1FFの(あいにく無効な)電子メールアドレス"
" B1FF\\@BIT.NET によって裏付けられている。"

#: ../../B/B1FF.rst:17
msgid ""
"[1993: Now It Can Be Told! My spies inform me that B1FF was originally "
"created by Joe Talmadge <jat@cup.hp.com>, also the author of the infamous "
"and much-plagiarized \"Flamer's Bible\". The BIFF filter he wrote was later "
"passed to Richard Sexton, who posted BIFFisms much more widely. Versions "
"have since been posted for the amusement of the net at large. See also "
":ref:`Jeff-K-` —ESR]"
msgstr ""
"[1993年:今や明かしてもよかろう! 私のスパイの報告によれば、B1FFはもともとJoe Talmadge "
"<jat@cup.hp.com>が作ったもので、彼は悪名高く大いに盗用された「Flamer's "
"Bible」の著者でもある。彼が書いたBIFFフィルターはのちにRichard "
"Sextonに渡され、SextonがBIFF語をはるかに広く投稿した。以来、ネット全体の楽しみのためにいくつかの版が投稿されている。\\ "
":ref:`Jeff-K-`\\ も参照。——ESR]"
